---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout
  title="Documentation"
  eyebrow="Docs"
  description="OpenPress is an agent-first document package: a shared base contract for skills, sources, page components, MDX documents, preview, validation, and export."
>

  <div class="doc-grid">
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/getting-started">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Start</p>
      <h3>Quick start</h3>
      <p>Two entry points: install skills and ask an agent, or run the CLI directly.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/product-boundary">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Start</p>
      <h3>Work with Agent</h3>
      <p>How agents should initialize, edit source, use skills, verify output, and stop at boundaries.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/skills">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Skills</p>
      <h3>AI agent integration</h3>
      <p>Built-in operational skills, authoring skills, starter-bearing skills, and external creative skills.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/themes">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Runtime</p>
      <h3>Themes</h3>
      <p>The <code>press/&lt;slug&gt;/theme/</code> and <code>press/shared/theme/</code> contract.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/sources">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Runtime</p>
      <h3>MDX sources</h3>
      <p>How <code>mdxSource()</code> and the <code>sources</code> export wire content into the engine.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/comments">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Runtime</p>
      <h3>Comment markers</h3>
      <p>Inline <code>@openpress-comment</code> markers — review flow without an external database.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/config">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Runtime</p>
      <h3>Workspace config</h3>
      <p>Where settings live — <code>&lt;Press&gt;</code> props, <code>package.json "openpress"</code>, and path conventions.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/cli">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">CLI</p>
      <h3>Commands</h3>
      <p>Three tiers — lifecycle (<code>init</code>/<code>dev</code>/<code>build</code>), output (<code>pdf</code>/<code>image</code>/<code>deploy</code>), tools (<code>search</code>/<code>inspect</code>/<code>doctor</code>).</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/public-api">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>Public API</h3>
      <p>The semver-covered exports, config fields, CSS variables, marker format, and dev endpoints.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/press">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>Press</h3>
      <p>The document entry — metadata via props, page tree via children. One per document.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/workspace">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>Workspace</h3>
      <p>Multi-document projects — proposal + pitch deck + social cards sharing brand &amp; data.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/frame">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>Frame</h3>
      <p>One fixed page surface. Covers, content pages, slides, and social cards are all Frames.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/text">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>Text</h3>
      <p>Styleless editable text objects for slides, cards, covers, captions, and component copy.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/mdx-area">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>MdxArea</h3>
      <p>A measurable slot inside a Frame that the engine fills with allocated blocks.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/manuscript">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>Manuscript helpers</h3>
      <p><code>Sections</code> + <code>Toc</code> — optional helpers for long-form section flow.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/use-source">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">API reference</p>
      <h3>useSource</h3>
      <p>Read a registered MDX source from inside the Press tree. Throws on unknown ids.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>Conventions</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Kind badge, invocation form, summary, props table, and an example on each API entry.</li>
    <li>Props tables: <em>name · type · default · description</em>.</li>
    <li>Anything outside the API pages — deep imports, internal helpers — is <strong>not</strong> covered by 1.0 stability.</li>
  </ul>
</DocLayout>

<style>
  .doc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(15rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--op-space-4);
    margin: var(--op-space-6) 0 var(--op-space-8);
  }

  .doc-card {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: var(--op-space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--op-hairline);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--op-surface) 84%, var(--op-paper));
    color: var(--op-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      border-color 140ms ease,
      transform 140ms ease,
      box-shadow 140ms ease;
  }
  .doc-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--op-accent);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 1rem 2rem color-mix(in srgb, var(--op-ink) 7%, transparent);
  }
  .doc-card__eyebrow {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--op-subdued);
    font-family: var(--op-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .doc-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--op-font-body);
    font-size: var(--op-text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--op-ink-strong);
  }
  .doc-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--op-subdued-strong);
    font-size: var(--op-text-sm);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .doc-card p code {
    padding: 0.06em 0.3em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--op-ink) 7%, transparent);
    font-family: var(--op-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
</style>
